text: Rare gem in Yishun. Wei Wei Noodle  Prawn noodles wife approve. 3 Chicken feet was presented to me. Carrot cake with lots of eggs. See for yourself. Generous hawker. Price is on the high side but compensated with more portion.
BLK 664 YishunAve food court. Nice tasting carrot cake, not that tasty char kuay teow thou.

This is a small neighbourhood coffee shop. Went there on Sunday morning. There is a noodle/carrot cake stall and another roast meat stall. The roast meat stall only have have duck ready. So basically there was only 1 stall open. Fortunately that stall has a large menu.

The place is airy and plenty seats. There is parking space nearby but looks like quite limited space.

hidden gems in this coffeeshop.

small corner stall selling economic beehoon with an old school taste. prices are very reasonable too.

Char kway teow here is a go to treat for myself when work gets tough even though it's a much further walk out.

If you like sweeter version of CKT then this is pretty decent. No wok hei but does its job well enough
